not receiving guests now, he will need to make himself available in the morning, 'cause there will be cameras out front and tabloids trying to get in the back.

229
00:15:34,101 --> 00:15:36,103
[CHATTERING, LAUGHING]

230
00:15:39,898 --> 00:15:40,941
Wait here.

231
00:15:46,572 --> 00:16:01,271
- [CHATTERING, LAUGHING CONTINUE]
- [EXHALES SHARPLY] Robert Hobden, as I live and breathe and shag like a lord.

232
00:16:01,295 --> 00:16:02,963
Good to see you, old chum.

233
00:16:03,630 --> 00:16:04,858
Timing's a little off.

234
00:16:04,882 --> 00:16:10,345
But when a friend drops
by, my door is always open, and my wine is waiting to be uncorked.

235
00:16:10,429 --> 00:16:12,309
I've got this, Seb. Give
us a moment, would you?

236
00:16:13,974 --> 00:16:16,661
What the fuck are you doing
here, you stupid fucking twat?

237
00:16:16,685 --> 00:16:18,955
[SIGHS] I have been
trying to contact you.

238
00:16:18,979 --> 00:16:22,542
I've been avoiding your calls. Take
the hint. You're fucking toxic.

239
00:16:22,566 --> 00:16:24,544
- Did anyone see you arrive?
- I don't know.

240
00:16:24,568 --> 00:16:27,821
- What kind of prick answer is that?
- It's the only prick answer I've got.

241
00:16:29,573 --> 00:16:33,553
- What happened?
- [SIGHS] Someone tried to kill me tonight.

242
00:16:33,577 --> 00:16:34,888
Well, a lot of fanatics about.

243
00:16:34,912 --> 00:16:37,849
- You're not the most popular...
- It wasn't a fanatic. It was a spook.

244
00:16:37,873 --> 00:16:38,957
- A spook?
- Mmm.

245
00:16:39,041 --> 00:16:43,253
MI5 sent a man, masked man, to my
flat, with a gun, to get my laptop.

246
00:16:43,337 --> 00:16:44,611
Fucking hell! I don't
know where anything is.

247
00:16:44,635 --> 00:16:46,548
I hardly ever come in here.

248
00:16:47,925 --> 00:16:50,320
Why would MI5 want
your computer?

249
00:16:50,344 --> 00:16:54,449
Because I have intel about the
kidnapping. The Muslim boy.

250
00:16:54,473 --> 00:16:56,034
Why should I care
about the kidnapping?

251
00:16:56,058 --> 00:16:59,454
I've already made enough of a tit
of myself, claiming it was ISIS.

252
00:16:59,478 --> 00:17:03,333
Because your entire career has
been playing the nationalist card.

253
00:17:03,357 --> 00:17:09,195
And if that boy dies, the closest
you'll get to Downing Street is looking down on it from an open-top bus.

254
00:17:34,012 --> 00:17:35,055
You alone?

255
00:17:38,684 --> 00:17:41,228
Don't know why they had
to clean up the canals.

256
00:17:42,855 --> 00:17:48,485
There was a time you
could find an oil drum or a corpse to use as a target.

257
00:17:58,412 --> 00:17:59,955
What do you think
you're playing at?

258
00:18:00,664 --> 00:18:06,879
Well, that's fucking choice,
considering I lent you an agent for what you said was a run-of-the-mill op, who now has a bullet in her head.

259
00:18:07,504 --> 00:18:11,401
"What do you think you're
playing at?" is my line, with a few fucking fucks thrown in.

260
00:18:11,425 --> 00:18:13,945
I'm sorry, but the brief was not
for her to be on Hobden 24/7.

261
00:18:13,969 --> 00:18:16,221
No, the brief was to
be on Cartwright 24/7.

262
00:18:16,305 --> 00:18:21,727
Which makes me think she
was your agent all along, and you were just asking for show.

263
00:18:23,478 --> 00:18:27,357
- Where was she when she was...
- She was shot outside Hobden's.

264
00:18:28,192 --> 00:18:33,488
Intentionally or otherwise, by Jed
Moody, another one of your recruits.

265
00:18:33,572 --> 00:18:37,177
So, if I may be so bold, what the living fuck do you think you're playing at?

266
00:18:37,201 --> 00:18:39,203
Check the rule book, Lamb.

267
00:18:39,912 --> 00:18:47,377
You run Slough
House, and God knows no one wants to take that away from you, but I am Second Desk, head of ops, which means directing personnel.

268
00:18:47,461 --> 00:18:50,380
All personnel. Yours
or anybody else's.

269
00:18:51,882 --> 00:18:55,028
[PASSES GAS, GRUNTS]
Better out than in.

270
00:18:55,052 --> 00:18:57,846
Oh, God, you're vile.

271
00:18:57,930 --> 00:19:00,390
[SNIFFS, GROANS]
Actually, maybe not.

272
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:08,815
So, say you're right and
this is none of my business, what do I do about the body on my staircase?

273
00:19:10,567 --> 00:19:11,985
- Moody?
- Yeah.

274
00:19:13,111 --> 00:19:14,112
He's dead?

275
00:19:14,196 --> 00:19:17,282
It's hard to tell,
given his IQ, but yes.

276
00:19:17,366 --> 00:19:18,635
- Jesus.
- Yeah.

277
00:19:18,659 --> 00:19:22,347
But if you wanted
to subcontract, you could've done better than Jed Moody.

278
00:19:22,371 --> 00:19:24,687
Even when he was good,
he wasn't any good.

279
00:19:24,711 --> 00:19:26,601
The guy's a fucking
fridge magnet.

280
00:19:26,625 --> 00:19:28,418
- Who took him down?
- W... [LAUGHS]

281
00:19:28,502 --> 00:19:31,606
Here's the funny part. He
forgot to tie his shoelaces.

282
00:19:31,630 --> 00:19:34,258
[LAUGHING] He f... He
fell down the stairs.

283
00:19:36,760 --> 00:19:40,973
Yes. When you're in
front of Limitations, you might want to leave out the bit about that being funny.

284
00:19:42,432 --> 00:19:44,017
Oh, Limitations.

285
00:19:45,811 --> 00:19:47,479
So, do we call in the Dogs?

286
00:19:47,563 --> 00:19:49,481
Hell, it's a death, Diana.

287
00:19:49,565 --> 00:19:52,192
I could call the
police. I should.

288
00:19:52,276 --> 00:19:54,212
I've got a mobile phone on me.

289
00:19:54,236 --> 00:19:56,256
Yeah, I could use that.

290
00:19:56,280 --> 00:19:58,073
Yeah, I found it
on Moody's body.

291
00:19:59,116 --> 00:20:01,743
The odd thing is, the only
number in it is yours.

292
00:20:01,827 --> 00:20:03,412
Yeah, you've made your point.

293
00:20:06,206 --> 00:20:07,976
It's after 02:00, Diana.

294
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:10,335
And my team is smaller
than it was yesterday.

295
00:20:10,419 --> 00:20:14,631
You've got till I finish this
fag before I start making calls.

296
00:20:17,176 --> 00:20:18,177
Okay.

297
00:20:19,845 --> 00:20:22,848
I was talking to my brother
at the Frontline Club.

298
00:20:24,057 --> 00:20:27,370
And I mentioned we were
developing operations to neutralize the nationalists.

299
00:20:27,394 --> 00:20:29,122
You are fucking kidding me.

300
00:20:29,146 --> 00:20:33,066
Sons of Albion have links to groups
all under Simmonds's umbrella.

301
00:20:33,150 --> 00:20:35,003
I can use this to
roll them all up.

302
00:20:35,027 --> 00:20:44,721
So, you set up some
half-arsed scheme involving a neofascist group kidnapping a Muslim kid and threatening to chop his head off on YouTube?

303
00:20:44,745 --> 00:20:47,849
Except it's not going to happen
'cause one of the group is yours.

304
00:20:47,873 --> 00:20:49,249
- Close?
- Half-arsed?

305
00:20:49,333 --> 00:20:52,562
One dead and one in
intensive care because what?

306
00:20:52,586 --> 00:20:55,172
You... You... You think Hobden's
got a piece of the puzzle?

307
00:20:56,715 --> 00:21:00,802
When I went to the bar
at the Frontline Club, I saw Hobden in the booth behind us.

308
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:04,681
Bad tradecraft on my
part, no... no question.

309
00:21:05,265 --> 00:21:08,852
Uh, you thought he might have
overheard you or recorded it?

310
00:21:08,936 --> 00:21:10,979
That's why you needed
to know what he had.

311
00:21:11,688 --> 00:21:12,689
[SCOFFS]

312
00:21:13,732 --> 00:21:15,919
[CHATTERING]

313
00:21:15,943 --> 00:21:17,152
Do you have any proof?

314
00:21:18,320 --> 00:21:21,591
No, but MI5 must think I do. That's
why they tried to kill me tonight.

315
00:21:21,615 --> 00:21:24,344
And you come here, leaving a
trail of mad, shitty footprints.

316
00:21:24,368 --> 00:21:28,181
- I don't want to be caught up in this.
- You're already caught up in this.

317
00:21:28,205 --> 00:21:30,999
You have to warn them
and get them out!

318
00:21:31,083 --> 00:21:32,167
And say what?

319
00:21:32,793 --> 00:21:38,006
Tell them that th-this whole setup,
this supposed execution, is a fake.

320
00:21:38,090 --> 00:21:43,905
That the Sons of Albion, who've never been more than a bunch of moronic street thugs, have been set up by the intelligence services.

321
00:21:43,929 --> 00:21:45,764
By an agent provocateur.

322
00:21:45,848 --> 00:21:48,141
And I'm to, what, announce
this in the House?

323
00:21:48,225 --> 00:21:49,369
Or maybe on the Today program?

324
00:21:49,393 --> 00:21:52,771
Peter, we've known each other for
years. Don't try and fob me off.

325
00:21:52,855 --> 00:21:54,624
We are not friends, Robert.

326
00:21:54,648 --> 00:21:56,835
You've always treated me fairly
in print, and I respect that.

327
00:21:56,859 --> 00:22:01,154
But let's face it, you're
a fucking has-been, and it's no longer appropriate to be associated with you.

328
00:22:02,197 --> 00:22:03,383
So take it somewhere else.

329
00:22:03,407 --> 00:22:05,552
Maybe to your pals in the
British Patriotic Party.

330
00:22:05,576 --> 00:22:07,160
[SCOFFS] What? They
won't believe me.

331
00:22:07,244 --> 00:22:10,497
Well, I can't warn these Sons of
Whatever. I don't know the fuckers.

332
00:22:10,581 --> 00:22:13,101
But you know people
who know people.

333
00:22:13,125 --> 00:22:15,085
You have to warn them.

334
00:22:15,169 --> 00:22:18,505
You have to get the word
out. A spy's in their midst.

335
00:22:18,589 --> 00:22:21,693
A rescue will be staged,
and they will all be killed.

336
00:22:21,717 --> 00:22:24,094
I'm a respected and
much-loved national figure.

337
00:22:24,178 --> 00:22:27,222
I don't have any of the contacts
you're talking about, you mad bastard.

338
00:22:27,306 --> 00:22:28,765
[SPOUSE] Peter, you're needed!

339
00:22:30,184 --> 00:22:33,705
The second I go upstairs, you get the fuck out of here, or I'll have Seb drag you out.

340
00:22:33,729 --> 00:22:35,415
I have the photo of
you at the rally.

341
00:22:35,439 --> 00:22:39,586
Darling, Nahim and Ursula
are going to go very soon.

342
00:22:39,610 --> 00:22:42,881
Already? And skipping cheese,
are they? I'll see about that.

343
00:22:42,905 --> 00:22:44,948
Let's open some port
and tempt them to stay.

344
00:22:45,449 --> 00:22:47,242
Would your friend
care to join us?

345
00:22:47,300 --> 00:22:50,388
Rob and I have been discussing some very official secret hush-hush, darling.

346
00:22:50,412 --> 00:22:52,122
No one's supposed
to know he's here.

347
00:22:52,873 --> 00:22:54,249
You wait here, bud.

348
00:22:54,333 --> 00:22:57,544
I'll settle things upstairs
and be back in a jiffy.

349
00:23:02,716 --> 00:23:03,759
[SIGHS]

350
00:23:04,843 --> 00:23:14,728
I can't help but notice you
seem, you know, pretty relaxed for someone who set up a false flag operation to behead an innocent kid in what, uh, four hours.

351
00:23:15,270 --> 00:23:16,563
They're not gonna do it.

352
00:23:16,647 --> 00:23:19,441
Their core messaging
suggests they very much are.

353
00:23:19,525 --> 00:23:22,152
Our agent told them they didn't
actually need a beheading.

354
00:23:22,236 --> 00:23:24,738
They just had to show that
they could do it if pushed.

355
00:23:25,572 --> 00:23:27,991
That's a hell of a gamble.
I wouldn't fancy your odds.

356
00:23:28,075 --> 00:23:29,326
You underestimate me.

357
00:23:30,410 --> 00:23:31,662
The boy was chosen with care.

358
00:23:33,539 --> 00:23:34,790
The kid. Who is he?

359
00:23:35,374 --> 00:23:37,936
He's Mahmud Gul's
nephew. Gul is...

360
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:40,814
I know who Mahmud
fucking Gul is.

361
00:23:40,838 --> 00:23:44,025
He's number two in Pakistan's
military intelligence.

362
00:23:44,049 --> 00:23:45,592
And... And this gets you what?

363
00:23:45,676 --> 00:23:52,075
We will rescue his nephew, and if that gets us even 10% more cooperation with the Pakistanis, it will be worth it.

364
00:23:52,099 --> 00:23:57,372
If this goes tits up... and Christ
knows it hasn't gone right yet you... you've assassinated his nephew!

365
00:23:57,396 --> 00:24:00,148
- Our man is...
- Oh, "your man."

366
00:24:00,941 --> 00:24:03,378
This isn't a sanctioned
service op, Diana.

367
00:24:03,402 --> 00:24:05,046
This is off the books!

368
00:24:05,070 --> 00:24:08,866
This is pirate shit! Now
you've got Hobden in the wind!

369
00:24:10,075 --> 00:24:11,243
You gotta roll this up!

370
00:24:12,536 --> 00:24:13,930
- It can still work.
- It...

371
00:24:13,954 --> 00:24:17,958
- This can neutralize the far right.
- [STAMMERS] It can't.

372
00:24:23,797 --> 00:24:26,341
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC
PLAYING ON TV]

373
00:24:27,801 --> 00:24:30,637
[HASSAN SNORING ON MONITOR]

374
00:24:32,639 --> 00:24:34,558
[SIGHS]

375
00:24:35,350 --> 00:24:37,102
How the fuck is he sleepin'?

376
00:24:37,644 --> 00:24:40,772
I know I couldn't sleep
with what he thinks is about to happen. I know that.

377
00:24:42,733 --> 00:24:44,568
He won't have slept
since we grabbed him.

378
00:24:45,694 --> 00:24:47,297
He must be exhausted.

379
00:24:47,321 --> 00:24:49,489
You wanna go down and sing
him a lullaby, do you?

380
00:24:49,573 --> 00:24:51,134
[ZEPPO CHUCKLES]

381
00:24:51,158 --> 00:24:53,493
[SNORING CONTINUES]

382
00:24:55,996 --> 00:24:56,997
Fuck's sake.

383
00:24:57,497 --> 00:24:59,666
[SIGHS] I'll mute it.

384
00:25:01,043 --> 00:25:02,187
Can still see the lights.

385
00:25:02,211 --> 00:25:04,272
[TV PLAYING, INDISTINCT]

386
00:25:04,296 --> 00:25:06,191
[IMITATING SNORING]

387
00:25:06,215 --> 00:25:08,300
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

388
00:25:23,148 --> 00:25:24,733
[SNIFFLES]

389
00:25:25,901 --> 00:25:28,028
[IMITATING SNORING CONTINUES]

390
00:25:34,117 --> 00:25:35,285
[OBJECT SCRAPING]

391
00:25:43,752 --> 00:25:45,796
[GRUNTS, PANTS]

392
00:25:46,755 --> 00:25:48,131
[STRAINING]

393
00:25:48,215 --> 00:25:49,508
[WOOD SNAPS, CLATTERS]

394
00:25:50,509 --> 00:25:51,927
- Little fucker!
- Bastard!

395
00:25:52,594 --> 00:25:53,971
Come on then.

396
00:25:56,223 --> 00:26:01,186
- Get down there.
- [PANTING] Help! Somebody help me!

397
00:26:01,270 --> 00:26:03,206
[GRUNTS] Somebody
help me, please!

398
00:26:03,230 --> 00:26:04,541
- [LARRY] Grab his legs!
- [MOE] No, no.

399
00:26:04,565 --> 00:26:07,442
- Somebody help me! Oh, no, no!
- [LARRY] Get him down from there!

400
00:26:07,526 --> 00:26:10,696
- [SCREAMS] Help me! Help me! Help!
- [MOE] Get the fucker out of here.

401
00:26:13,448 --> 00:26:15,117
Just humor me and
explore the flip side.

402
00:26:15,701 --> 00:26:20,515
If those Sons of Nonsense get
wind of what you're up to, that kid is as good as dead, and your man too.

403
00:26:20,539 --> 00:26:22,916
You've gotta call him and
tell him his cover's blown.

404
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:25,687
Not possible. He wanted
them to go dark. No phones.

405
00:26:25,711 --> 00:26:28,297
[STAMMERS] Send
in the Dogs early.

406
00:26:28,881 --> 00:26:33,343
If we bring it forward,
we need to let him know so he can secure Hassan and get out himself.

407
00:26:33,427 --> 00:26:35,822
- Yeah. Well, lots of luck with that one.
- You're gonna help me.

408
00:26:35,846 --> 00:26:38,366
Ugh. Oh, no, I'm not. And
nor are any of my people.

409
00:26:38,390 --> 00:26:39,766
They brought the boy to London.

410
00:26:39,850 --> 00:26:42,102
They're holding him in a
house this side of the river.

411
00:26:42,186 --> 00:26:44,831
All I'm asking you to do is
literally knock on the door.

412
00:26:44,855 --> 00:26:46,523
Our man will answer, and...

413
00:26:47,649 --> 00:26:49,943
- What's the signal?
- Your face is the signal.

414
00:26:50,777 --> 00:26:51,963
My face?

415
00:26:51,987 --> 00:26:54,573
Oh, you're a legend in
the service, Jackson.

416
00:26:55,407 --> 00:26:58,493
He'll recognize your face and
know something's about to go down.

417
00:26:58,577 --> 00:27:01,681
He'll secure Hassan, and Dogs
will be right behind you.

418
00:27:01,705 --> 00:27:03,790
They'll go in and
do the dirty work.

419
00:27:06,543 --> 00:27:09,022
I've got other things I
could do tonight, Diana.

420
00:27:09,046 --> 00:27:12,150
[SNIFFLES] I've got a
really massive shit brewin'.

421
00:27:12,174 --> 00:27:14,968
I could sit and read a
book and birth that beauty.

422
00:27:15,052 --> 00:27:17,221
[SIGHS]

423
00:27:19,473 --> 00:27:21,058
Was Moody alone when he died?

424
00:27:21,808 --> 00:27:24,269
We're all alone in the end,
don't you think, Diana?

425
00:27:24,353 --> 00:27:25,854
In those final moments?

426
00:27:25,938 --> 00:27:31,401
If he did have company, that company might come under intense scrutiny.

427
00:27:31,485 --> 00:27:33,338
Oh, by all means,
call in the Dogs.

428
00:27:33,362 --> 00:27:38,343
And when they're finished
tearing you apart, maybe they'll have enough strength to pick at the rest of this.

429
00:27:38,367 --> 00:27:40,619
Either way, I couldn't
give a monkey's.

430
00:27:41,286 --> 00:27:43,080
Even if it was Standish?

431
00:27:45,791 --> 00:27:48,353
Y... You're tossin' darts.

432
00:27:48,377 --> 00:27:50,814
Standish wasn't there.
She's at home asleep.

433
00:27:50,838 --> 00:27:52,649
I'm not talking about tonight.

434
00:27:52,673 --> 00:27:55,592
I'm talking about the
night Charles Partner died.

435
00:27:56,510 --> 00:28:00,764
Catherine Standish came very
close to a treason charge.

436
00:28:01,849 --> 00:28:04,369
That file could be
reopened, reassessed.

437
00:28:04,393 --> 00:28:06,895
Didn't fly then.
It won't fly now.

438
00:28:06,979 --> 00:28:08,939
A lot of other things
might come out.

439
00:28:12,484 --> 00:28:15,737
That is not a can of
worms you want to open.

440
00:28:15,821 --> 00:28:17,489
Do I look keen?

441
00:28:20,576 --> 00:28:22,971
Like it or not, Slough
House is part of this now.

442
00:28:22,995 --> 00:28:25,163
You'll all get turned over.

443
00:28:25,247 --> 00:28:29,210
Standish will find
out some things it would be better for her not to know.

444
00:28:41,388 --> 00:28:43,348
I'll go knock on
the door for you.

445
00:28:45,809 --> 00:28:49,605
But in return, I want
the Standish file.

446
00:28:52,482 --> 00:28:57,255
And you've been using Slough
House as your personal toy box, which pisses me off.

447
00:28:57,279 --> 00:28:58,780
- Are we clear?
- Crystal.

448
00:28:58,864 --> 00:29:00,073
Oh, there's more.

449
00:29:01,700 --> 00:29:03,577
Moody disappears.

450
00:29:04,745 --> 00:29:07,706
Baker, a victim of street crime.

451
00:29:08,540 --> 00:29:11,376
Anyone with me
tonight is fireproof.

452
00:29:11,460 --> 00:29:12,461
